<L>__{interior night. thornfield the hall.}
<A>__{adele and jane sit on the stairs, listening to blanche and rochester sing. their voices thrill. jane is trying not to feel. but when rochester hits an exceptionally beautiful note, she involuntarily closes her eyes. adele leans into jane. she is crying.}
<C>__{jane}
<D>__{what is it, darling?}
<C>__{adele}
<D>__{she sing like maman.}
<A>__{jane, full of compassion, takes adele back to her room.}
<L>__{interior day. thornfield the schoolroom.}
<A>__{mrs fairfax enters in a great hurry.}
<C>__{mrs fairfax}
<D>__{tonight. he wants you both in the drawing room after dinner.}
<A>__{adele leaps up, delighted. jane is crestfallen.}
<C>__{jane}
<D>__{not me, surely.}
<C>__{mrs fairfax}
<D>__{it's his particular wish.}
<C>__{jane}
<D>__{he was being polite.}
<C>__{mrs fairfax}
<D>__{i'm instructed to tell you that if you resist, he'll come up and get you himself. you needn't stay long. just let him see you and then slip away. don't worry; no one'll look at you.}
